A fatal auto accident along Ilorin- Ogbomoso expressway, on Sunday, claimed the lives of seven persons. The accident, which involved a single vehicle, occurred at Otte village in Asa local government area of Kwara State at about 3.30am. LEADERSHIP gathered that the accident involving a Mazda bus with registration number ZUR 159 XJ and loaded with 28 people, was caused by over-speeding, overloading and tyre burst. The state sector commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Jonathan Owoade, who confirmed the accident, said that the crash was due to tyre burst and loss of control. He said both the injured victims and the dead bodies have been taken to the General Hospital in Ilorin, the state capital. “We received help from the State Ministry of Health. They gave us Ambulance to support our own Ambulance to evacuate the victims to the hospital,” Owoade stated.